<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-1')">1</a>. The site is unable to structurally deal with the influx of new would-be authors and the maintenance this requires. For example, the draft forms are stressfully overwhelmed. The time it takes a series to fill up is telescoping over time, the last one (series 4 at the time of writing) taking little over a year compared to several years for previous series. While this can be attributed to record high numbers of sure membership (and presumably more quality authors and articles in the mix), it can also be attributed to a general laxing of the standards for the product, such that the site’s forte is a redundancy of compositional homogeny.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-2')">2</a>. These votes are published publicly.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-3"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-3')">3</a>. Partially by virtue of their desire for it in the first place.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-4"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-4')">4</a>. Generally speaking; there are those in authority and even at the heights of it who have decried the community’s turn away from compositional standards to consumptive ones. This is documented.</div>
