<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-6"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-6')">6</a>. Case in point.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-7"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-7')">7</a>. This module must be positioned so as to be seen as the first part of an article (literally higher up than any other text), denying the reader both any choice of independent approach and, excluding those who can &quot;unsee&quot; a rating enough to judge the content for the raw quality that it is, a fair chance at community-valuation.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-8"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-8')">8</a>. What is the <em>one</em> nidus of power on the site? <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Name</span> Brand recognition. Anybody who is anybody on this site is terrified of one thing: losing their <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">name</span> brand. Users are under constant threat of marginalization and banishment by both the ruling class for disciplinary reasons, and by the consumption classes for political ones. An unsuccessful work is sometimes very quickly given up on and deleted by its author (especially ruling-class authors) for the sake of optics.</div>
